main event: An unidentified object was observed by several witnesses in Finland, Minnesota on 2 November 1957.
interesting points: The object was described as almost oval shaped and cloudlike, but its movements eliminated it as a cloud., The observation lasted between 1 to 3 hours., The weather conditions were clear and calm with a bright moon present., Witnesses concluded that the object was likely the planet Venus due to its brightness and position., The documentation references military involvement in the investigation of this sighting.
witness description: Witnesses reported the object for 1 to 3 hours under clear weather conditions.
